finding: Cryo-EM analysis reveals the structure of apo and holo HCoV-OC43 S glycoprotein at 2.9 and 2.8 Å resolution, respectively (Supplementary Fig. 1).
HCoV-OC43 S recognizes carbohydrate ligands through distinct regions, similar to human galectin-3 and rotavirus VP8* β-sandwich (Supplementary Fig. 2).
Free 9-O-Ac-Me-Sia receptor does not trigger fusogenic conformational changes in HCoV-OC43 S (Supplementary Fig. 4).
Coronavirus S galectin-like A domains have a conserved architecture (Supplementary Fig. 5).
Trypsin cleavage of HCoV-OC43 S followed by heating at 50°C in the presence of isopropanol leads to the formation of postfusion rosettes (Supplementary Fig. 4).
